<div id="c17">
<p>I have a book (ISBN 0-13-165945-6) that suggests free will is an illusion; using a computer-science complexity argument.</p>

<p>Like a computer of finite speed your mind has not enough capacity to simulate itself in real time (the circuits used for the simulation necessarily being somewhat less than the whole).  Hence possible determinism while being unable to know your own future.</p>

