<div id="c26">
<p>What does chaos theory have to do with randomness? Fractals are completely deterministic, yet you still can’t predict what any part will look like.</p>

<p>Determinism does not equal predictability. This whole debate seems pretty narrow-minded and pedestrian to me.</p>

<p>We know today that the way thinking works is roughly by firing neuron patterns that feed back until a signal has sufficiently self-amplified to cross a threshold. The brain is a pattern matcher driven by innumerable feedback loops – a boundlessly non-linear system.</p>

<p>So what if it’s deterministic? It won’t do you any good to know that it is.</p>

